    "body": "In Template Strings:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n// good\r\nfunction sayHi(name) {\r\n  return `How are you, ${name}?`;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nDo you prefer `${name}` over `${ name }` ?\r\n\r\nFor variables that seems obvious (no space), but template strings allows much more, like `${ (name) ? name : 'No name' }`, where i think spacing makes it more clear.\r\n\r\n> I didn't test that expression, i can be wrong :stuck_out_tongue:\r\n"
